      "content": "gotcha. so i should avoid a list of chunks. i'm still seeing these weird spikes though, like it'll be fine and then suddenly my system just feels totally starved of resources for a second before it crashes. is there any way to track down what's \"stealing\" the memory if it's not an obvious big list? i'm trying to figure out if something is slowly consuming it in the background.",
