      "content": "To track down unexpected memory usage spikes, you should use system profiling tools. Tools like `memory_profiler` can be used to decorate your functions and report memory usage line-by-line, showing you exactly which line of code is causing the consumption. You can also use OS-level tools like `top` or `htop` while the script is running to monitor the Python process's memory footprint dynamically. This will help pinpoint if the spike is related to garbage collection, intermediate object creation, or some slow accumulation.",
